WEBVTT

00:03.037 --> 00:05.939
I want to start
my fucking private club!

00:05.973 --> 00:07.741
And I want you to be my partner.

00:07.775 --> 00:12.313
The goal is to only deal with
a few high-level customers.

00:12.346 --> 00:14.948
They buy the coke,
they cook the rock theyselves.

00:14.982 --> 00:16.450
All we gotta do is deliver
and collect.

00:16.484 --> 00:17.818
CISSY:
We lost the property.

00:17.851 --> 00:19.820
It's not one we wanted to lose.

00:19.853 --> 00:21.855
ANDRE:
Captain, this is something new.

00:21.889 --> 00:23.757
It's called "rock."

00:23.791 --> 00:25.259
And it's expanding
beyond my neighborhood,

00:25.293 --> 00:26.694
and moving up towards
the Coliseum.

00:26.727 --> 00:27.961
What are you suggesting?

00:27.995 --> 00:30.998
You and me, we at war.

00:31.031 --> 00:33.334
-Your men ready to roll,
Sergeant?
-Yes, sir, Lieutenant.

00:33.367 --> 00:35.035
Let's go.
Hook 'em and book 'em!

00:35.069 --> 00:39.840
(overlapping shouting)

00:39.873 --> 00:41.008
-(gun cocks)
-Do not move!

00:41.041 --> 00:43.144
-Get your hands off...
-(screaming)

00:43.177 --> 00:45.279
(overlapping shouting)

00:45.313 --> 00:46.714
LOUIE:
Fuck you!

00:46.747 --> 00:49.049
You need to be thinking about
how you're gonna handle Andre.

00:49.083 --> 00:50.884
ALTON:
I know how this feels.

00:50.918 --> 00:52.953
How bad you must want
to get back.

00:52.986 --> 00:54.522
But you can't kill no cop.

00:54.555 --> 00:57.825
I'm talking about the hell

00:57.858 --> 01:01.162
that will be rained down
upon black folks

01:01.195 --> 01:04.498
if that happens.

01:04.532 --> 01:07.535
-Franklin, please, just listen.
-Get the fuck out of here

01:07.568 --> 01:09.670
before I call her back.

01:14.842 --> 01:17.411
REPORTER (over TV):
...mindset and why detectives

01:17.445 --> 01:20.248
across several states were
unable to share information

01:20.281 --> 01:21.449
that might have
prevented further...

01:21.482 --> 01:24.218
So, where did you find this kid?

01:24.252 --> 01:25.586
TEDDY:
Through Avi.

01:25.619 --> 01:27.588
Right, the arms dealer.

01:27.621 --> 01:31.425
Yeah. But before that,
he was buying product off me.

01:31.459 --> 01:32.760
REPORTER 2 (over TV):
LAPD Chief...

01:32.793 --> 01:36.264
Hey, look, I know you have
a job to do here.

01:36.297 --> 01:39.867
I get that. But...

01:39.900 --> 01:41.169
you have to protect my assets.

01:41.202 --> 01:43.371
You can't share their names
with the D.O.

01:43.404 --> 01:45.739
And you think if you keep
saying it over and over,

01:45.773 --> 01:48.809
it will increase my chances
of listening to you?

01:48.842 --> 01:51.245
Because they won't.

01:51.279 --> 01:52.713
What the hell?

01:52.746 --> 01:54.382
SPOKESPERSON (over TV):
...executed four simultaneous

01:54.415 --> 01:56.717
drug raids on various locations

01:56.750 --> 01:58.219
in the South Central region.

01:58.252 --> 02:02.323
These raids resulted in 14
arrests, as well as the seizure

02:02.356 --> 02:06.294
of over 20 kilograms of
cocaine, rock cocaine,

02:06.327 --> 02:08.629
and a variety of
high-caliber weapons,

02:08.662 --> 02:09.897
including a submachine gun.

02:09.930 --> 02:11.599
Jesus.

02:11.632 --> 02:13.434
At this time, I'd like to
turn it over to the officer

02:13.467 --> 02:15.703
who led the raids,
our own Sergeant Andre Wright.

02:17.938 --> 02:19.640
Andre Wright?

02:19.673 --> 02:23.877
Isn't that the arresting officer
on Saint's murder charge?

02:23.911 --> 02:26.180
ANDRE:
...37th Street Division.

02:26.214 --> 02:30.484
These seizures are a huge
victory in our ongoing fight

02:30.518 --> 02:32.486
against dangerous weapons
and drugs.

02:32.520 --> 02:34.655
And we all need to stay
vigilant, united...

02:34.688 --> 02:36.457
-This a problem?
-...and alert

02:36.490 --> 02:38.959
in our fight against crime.

02:38.992 --> 02:40.628
NEWSWOMAN (over TV):
When we return...

02:40.661 --> 02:43.397
*

02:54.375 --> 02:58.111
* They call me Big Bad John *

02:58.145 --> 03:01.849
Seriously, man,
this is your victory.

03:01.882 --> 03:03.817
You own this.

03:03.851 --> 03:06.520
All right?
So let's give it up, men.

03:06.554 --> 03:09.857
-To Sergeant Wright!
-(all cheer)

03:09.890 --> 03:11.892
Mm!

03:13.827 --> 03:15.663
Hey. Two shots of Cuervo,
my man.

03:15.696 --> 03:17.865
Oh, no, no, I'm good.
Thank you.

03:17.898 --> 03:20.534
Oh, the hell you are.
You are taking a shot, Sergeant.

03:20.568 --> 03:22.236
That is an order.

03:22.270 --> 03:23.404
I outrank you.

03:23.437 --> 03:25.306
(laughs)
Not in these parts you don't.

03:25.339 --> 03:27.808
Let's go!

03:27.841 --> 03:29.209
* They call me Big Bad John... *

03:29.243 --> 03:31.245
-Uh-- Hey!
-Oh.

03:31.279 --> 03:32.413
-Oh, shit.
-(sighs)

03:32.446 --> 03:34.114
I'm sorry, honey. Here.

03:34.147 --> 03:35.683
-I got you-- Whoa!
-Excuse me!

03:35.716 --> 03:38.852
Easy, princess.
I said I was sorry.

03:38.886 --> 03:40.254
Yeah, you're a real gentleman.

03:40.288 --> 03:41.389
ANDRE:
Why don't you go outside, man?

03:41.422 --> 03:43.156
-Have a smoke.
-What the hell is your problem?

03:43.190 --> 03:44.992
-Get some fresh air.
-All right, all right,
all right, all right.

03:45.025 --> 03:47.227
Hey, I'm so sorry.

03:47.261 --> 03:49.196
Your friend always act
like that?

03:49.229 --> 03:52.132
Uh, he had a few too many,
but, uh,

03:52.165 --> 03:53.634
we're here celebrating.

03:53.667 --> 03:55.002
Yeah, I noticed.

03:55.035 --> 03:57.771
Anyway, I'm really sorry.

03:57.805 --> 03:59.540
(sighs)
What are you celebrating?

03:59.573 --> 04:01.542
You win a softball game
or something?

04:01.575 --> 04:04.111
(chuckles)

04:04.144 --> 04:07.448
Yeah. Something like that.

04:07.481 --> 04:09.383
I'm Sheila.

04:09.417 --> 04:11.419
-Andre.
-Mm.

04:11.452 --> 04:15.389
You gonna buy me another drink
or what?

04:15.423 --> 04:16.424
-You're lying!
-(laughing)

04:16.457 --> 04:19.259
You're lying.
11 brothers and sisters?

04:19.293 --> 04:20.861
Mm. Yep.

04:20.894 --> 04:22.530
Seven girls, four boys.
(chuckles)

04:22.563 --> 04:24.532
Good lord. Oh, man.

04:24.565 --> 04:27.067
I mean, I'm raising one,
and I can barely handle it.

04:27.100 --> 04:29.202
Hey, it made me strong.

04:29.236 --> 04:30.371
I learned how to fend
for myself.

04:30.404 --> 04:32.740
Hey, be gentle with this one.

04:32.773 --> 04:33.907
He's a delicate little flower.

04:33.941 --> 04:36.744
-Get out of here, man!
-Okay.

04:36.777 --> 04:38.078
Let's go, boys!

04:40.113 --> 04:42.149
Sorry about that.

04:42.182 --> 04:44.151
You apologize
for your friend a lot.

04:44.184 --> 04:48.088
He's more of a coworker.
Barely even like the guy.

04:48.121 --> 04:51.158
-Hey, well,
that makes two of us.
-(chuckles)

05:03.504 --> 05:06.907
Where did you come from?

05:06.940 --> 05:09.109
I sure wish I could
take you home.

05:09.142 --> 05:10.511
Mm.

05:16.249 --> 05:17.418
What?

05:32.132 --> 05:33.300
Damn.

05:33.333 --> 05:35.536
Look at this place.

05:36.970 --> 05:37.971
You crooked or something?

05:38.005 --> 05:39.773
(scoffs)
What?

05:39.807 --> 05:42.109
-How's a cop afford this?
-Oh, well,

05:42.142 --> 05:44.011
this is a-a splurge, believe me.

05:44.044 --> 05:46.447
But it turns out,

05:46.480 --> 05:49.149
these'll get you
a nice discount.

06:04.665 --> 06:06.166
(Sheila moans softly)

06:10.538 --> 06:11.839
Why don't you get comfortable.

06:11.872 --> 06:13.841
I'll make us a nightcap.

06:25.853 --> 06:27.220
(knock on door)

06:27.254 --> 06:29.923
WOMAN:
Housekeeping.

06:29.957 --> 06:32.593
Housekeeping.

06:32.626 --> 06:34.628
(groans softly)

06:36.063 --> 06:37.465
(door opens)

06:37.498 --> 06:39.967
(door closes)

06:40.000 --> 06:41.869
Oh, sorry.
I'll-I'll come back.

06:41.902 --> 06:44.337
What?

06:44.371 --> 06:48.008
(door opens, closes)

06:48.041 --> 06:49.242
(exhales)

06:54.882 --> 06:56.784
(sighs heavily)

07:09.429 --> 07:11.164
*

07:30.784 --> 07:33.587
Mm. Give my love to Estelle.

07:33.621 --> 07:34.855
SHEILA:
I will.

07:34.888 --> 07:36.724
-Call me when you land.
-All right.

07:36.757 --> 07:38.959
-Be good, baby girl.
-I will.

07:38.992 --> 07:41.428
Thank you.

07:48.268 --> 07:49.369
You be good to her.

08:14.695 --> 08:16.697
*

08:48.061 --> 08:49.663
(engine turns off)

08:56.637 --> 08:57.838
'Sup, Reed?

08:57.871 --> 08:59.306
What's going on?

08:59.339 --> 09:03.811
What's going on is your business
all over the 5:00 news.

09:03.844 --> 09:06.079
We met up right after that shit
went down last week.

09:06.113 --> 09:08.215
You didn't think
that's worth mentioning?

09:08.248 --> 09:09.883
I didn't want to
trouble you with it.

09:09.917 --> 09:11.652
Oh, that's very considerate
of you, thank you.

09:11.685 --> 09:14.622
They found a fucking Uzi
on one of your guys.

09:14.655 --> 09:17.390
That tends to get
people's attention.

09:17.424 --> 09:19.526
This the business we in, Reed.

09:19.559 --> 09:22.195
I've come to learn that shit's
just gonna happen.

09:22.229 --> 09:24.765
You familiar with
the Dade County shootout?

09:26.133 --> 09:27.901
Few years ago, Miami.

09:27.935 --> 09:29.169
Cubans, Colombians decided
they were gonna

09:29.202 --> 09:31.538
shoot it out midday
in a crowded shopping center.

09:31.571 --> 09:34.007
Now, the cops found
an armored car disguised

09:34.041 --> 09:35.575
as a party truck,
assault weapons, ammunition

09:35.609 --> 09:37.077
all over the parking lot.

09:37.110 --> 09:39.012
And it changed everything
because it brought

09:39.046 --> 09:41.214
the federal government out
in force.

09:42.916 --> 09:45.018
That was the beginning of the
end of the easy cocaine days

09:45.052 --> 09:46.854
-in South Florida.
-Yeah, but...

09:46.887 --> 09:48.488
Come on, man, it was one Uzi.

09:48.521 --> 09:50.724
You're overthinking this shit.

09:50.758 --> 09:52.025
Am I?

09:52.059 --> 09:54.294
Yeah.

09:54.327 --> 09:57.631
You know the cop that led
the raid, Sergeant Wright?

09:57.665 --> 10:00.133
He's trying to get your
case file unsealed.

10:01.601 --> 10:04.071
Hmm.

10:04.104 --> 10:06.707
He's from my neighborhood.

10:06.740 --> 10:08.441
Known him my whole life.

10:08.475 --> 10:10.443
Things have got
a bit personal lately,

10:10.477 --> 10:13.046
-but again, I'm handling it.
-How?

10:13.080 --> 10:15.916
Seems it might be better
if you didn't know.

10:19.152 --> 10:23.023
Look, you can be involved
if you really want.

10:23.056 --> 10:26.827
But it'd be better for everyone
if you just trust me.

10:26.860 --> 10:28.996
Huh?

10:34.634 --> 10:37.570
Okay.

10:37.604 --> 10:40.640
I'll be in touch soon
about next week's drop.

10:44.611 --> 10:45.813
Hey, Franklin?

10:47.647 --> 10:49.582
Good luck.

10:56.323 --> 10:58.325
(car door closes, engine starts)

11:08.068 --> 11:10.337
LOUIE:
Terrence in Gardena's
good for ten.

11:10.370 --> 11:12.072
FRANKLIN:
All right.

11:12.105 --> 11:14.174
Uh, Mookie said he can move
about five a week,

11:14.207 --> 11:16.109
maybe more, depending.

11:16.143 --> 11:18.678
All right, cool.

11:18.712 --> 11:21.281
So it's about 80 a week.

11:21.314 --> 11:23.483
What about Inglewood?

11:27.054 --> 11:29.923
What? Ain't nobody got
no connects in Inglewood?

11:31.258 --> 11:34.762
Ain't nothing going through
no goddamn Inglewood...

11:34.795 --> 11:35.963
without Skully.

11:35.996 --> 11:37.998
Skully. (chuckles) And?

11:38.031 --> 11:40.200
And we ain't got no connections
with Skully.

11:41.234 --> 11:43.603
Well, we kind of do.

11:43.636 --> 11:45.405
-Shut up, nigga.
-What?

11:45.438 --> 11:47.875
-Nigga, we do.
-What you talking about,
Fatback?

11:47.908 --> 11:49.442
Manboy.

11:49.476 --> 11:51.711
His sister is Skully's baby
mama. They stay in The Bottoms.

11:51.745 --> 11:52.880
(Franklin chuckles)

11:52.913 --> 11:55.715
Well, ain't that something.

11:55.749 --> 11:57.851
Leon, I need you
to link up with Manboy,

11:57.885 --> 11:59.386
-go handle that shit.
-Hell no.

11:59.419 --> 12:00.988
Hey, that shit
with Wanda's been dealt with.

12:01.021 --> 12:02.622
Okay? I ain't asking you

12:02.655 --> 12:05.258
to be that nigga's best friend,
but this is business,

12:05.292 --> 12:06.960
and I need you
to handle this shit.

12:06.994 --> 12:10.397
-All right?
-All right.

12:10.430 --> 12:12.800
FRANKLIN:
Good.

12:12.833 --> 12:15.202
All right, that's it for now.
Let's make this money.

12:17.237 --> 12:19.873
-Hey, nephew.
-(indistinct chatter)

12:19.907 --> 12:22.342
Hey, man.
Let me talk to you for a minute.

12:22.375 --> 12:23.811
Can it wait?

12:23.844 --> 12:26.579
Got to go see my moms, man,
already late.

12:26.613 --> 12:30.017
Okay.

12:30.050 --> 12:31.718
How you feeling?

12:33.086 --> 12:34.888
Looks worse than it is.

12:37.891 --> 12:40.193
Go on, man.

12:40.227 --> 12:42.262
All right.

12:42.295 --> 12:45.999
-I'm-a talk to you later.
-Yeah.

12:58.611 --> 13:01.048
Come in when you're done,
Sergeant.

13:04.417 --> 13:06.153
TODD:
It's not a good look,

13:06.186 --> 13:07.955
-Sergeant.
-The only thing that makes sense

13:07.988 --> 13:10.557
is that she drugged me.

13:10.590 --> 13:13.260
So what do you know
about this broad?

13:13.293 --> 13:15.795
-You ever seen her before?
-Can't say I have.

13:15.829 --> 13:19.499
What kind of drugs
were you two taking?

13:19.532 --> 13:23.904
What? No, I wasn't taking drugs.
I was drugged.

13:23.937 --> 13:27.074
Right. Right, sorry.

13:27.107 --> 13:29.176
(clears throat)
But, unfortunately,

13:29.209 --> 13:30.911
I'm gonna have to
bump this up to I.A.

13:30.944 --> 13:34.614
-(sighs) I.A.? For this?
-Yeah, I'm afraid so.

13:34.647 --> 13:37.284
My hands are kind of tied
on this one.

13:37.317 --> 13:39.119
If people see me
making exceptions

13:39.152 --> 13:40.453
for the big TV star,

13:40.487 --> 13:42.489
I mean, how's that gonna look?

13:44.791 --> 13:45.993
Mmm.

13:52.532 --> 13:54.968
-Hold up. You're not eating?
-I'm not hungry.

14:02.742 --> 14:04.144
You worried about the raids?

14:04.177 --> 14:05.812
The shit that happened
with Jerome?

14:05.845 --> 14:07.314
I don't want to talk about that.

14:08.982 --> 14:11.484
You know, all I'm saying
is we good.

14:11.518 --> 14:13.053
You know, there's nothing
that connects us.

14:13.086 --> 14:15.222
What did I say?

14:17.257 --> 14:18.992
All right.

14:22.029 --> 14:24.331
Let's talk real estate, then.

14:24.364 --> 14:28.969
Huh? You find out who outbid us
on that property?

14:29.002 --> 14:30.403
I did.

14:33.073 --> 14:35.708
And you're not gonna believe it.

14:41.214 --> 14:44.551
Where have you been?
I called the department.

14:44.584 --> 14:47.154
-Nobody knew where you were.
-I'm sorry, I...

14:47.187 --> 14:49.189
I'm fine.
I was just with the guys.

14:49.222 --> 14:52.025
-All night?
-Yeah.

14:52.059 --> 14:54.327
I had a few too many
and didn't want to drive,

14:54.361 --> 14:57.564
so I slept on Nix's couch.

14:57.597 --> 14:59.566
Daddy, it's 1:00
in the afternoon.

14:59.599 --> 15:02.335
You couldn't call me?

15:02.369 --> 15:04.604
I know, and I'm sorry.
I wasn't thinking.

15:04.637 --> 15:08.041
I thought something happened
to you. If I had done

15:08.075 --> 15:09.709
something like this,
you would've lost your mind,

15:09.742 --> 15:12.212
-had the whole department
looking for me.
-Because you're a child.

15:12.245 --> 15:14.881
And I'm the man of the house,
and I don't need to be

15:14.914 --> 15:17.650
-interrogated in my own home.
-Well, excuse me for worrying.

15:21.454 --> 15:24.724
-(refrigerator opens)
-A-Are you hungry?

15:24.757 --> 15:26.693
(sighs)

15:26.726 --> 15:28.795
You want me to fix you
something to eat?

15:28.828 --> 15:32.832
No. I just need
to get some sleep.

15:32.865 --> 15:34.601
(bottle opens)

15:40.807 --> 15:43.943
Uh... You know you left your bag

15:43.977 --> 15:46.079
sitting on top of the car.

15:46.113 --> 15:48.115
Oh, shit.

16:04.497 --> 16:06.499
(indistinct chatter in distance)

16:14.141 --> 16:16.143
*

16:28.821 --> 16:32.192
(car door closes, engine starts)

16:51.311 --> 16:53.313
(indistinct chatter nearby)

16:57.084 --> 16:59.286
You want to put your eyes
back in your head?

16:59.319 --> 17:00.520
(intercom beeps)

17:00.553 --> 17:02.589
TULFOWITZ:
Send them in.

17:02.622 --> 17:04.824
Mr. Tulfowitz will see you now.

17:10.497 --> 17:12.699
Thank you.
(clears throat)

17:19.706 --> 17:22.875
Well, there she is.

17:24.911 --> 17:26.546
Hello, Cissy.

17:26.579 --> 17:29.516
-(chuckles)
-Hello, Arnold.

17:29.549 --> 17:32.018
Franklin, good to see you, son.

17:32.051 --> 17:34.187
Whoa.

17:34.221 --> 17:36.523
It's been a while. (laughs)

17:36.556 --> 17:38.658
Have a seat. Have a seat,
please. Please, sit down.

17:38.691 --> 17:41.561
(chuckles)

17:41.594 --> 17:43.563
So...

17:43.596 --> 17:46.533
to what do I owe the pleasure?

17:46.566 --> 17:49.702
We want to talk to you about
the property on South Avalon.

17:49.736 --> 17:52.772
-Really?
-Yeah.

17:52.805 --> 17:55.242
We're hoping you might
rescind your offer.

17:57.310 --> 18:00.447
You two were hoping
I might rescind my offer?

18:00.480 --> 18:02.415
-Mm-hmm.
-Why would I do that?

18:02.449 --> 18:03.916
Money,

18:03.950 --> 18:06.153
of course.

18:06.186 --> 18:08.020
We'll make it worth your while.

18:08.054 --> 18:10.423
You were the other bidder.

18:10.457 --> 18:13.660
You were why I paid 40K

18:13.693 --> 18:15.595
over asking. (chuckles)

18:15.628 --> 18:18.097
Son of a bitch.

18:18.131 --> 18:21.067
(laughs) And here I was
thinking you were coming in

18:21.100 --> 18:22.702
to beg for your old job back.

18:22.735 --> 18:25.205
(laughs)

18:25.238 --> 18:28.508
(laughs)
No. I work for myself now.

18:28.541 --> 18:30.777
Well, good for you.

18:30.810 --> 18:33.746
Look, we're willing to cut you
a check for $50,000

18:33.780 --> 18:36.849
-just to walk away.
-50 grand, huh?

18:36.883 --> 18:38.285
CISSY:
Arnold,

18:38.318 --> 18:41.087
we have a vested interest
in the property.

18:41.120 --> 18:42.822
We'd like to build up
the community.

18:42.855 --> 18:44.857
Provide decent housing
for low income families.

18:44.891 --> 18:47.894
Well, that's very commendable,

18:47.927 --> 18:50.129
but if you want it so bad,

18:50.163 --> 18:51.398
why didn't you just make
